                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>Sir <forename>William</forename> de <surname>Aton</surname>, kt., sen.</persName>, 
                   appoints <persName>sir <forename>Richard</forename> de <surname>Hoton</surname>, chaplain</persName>, 
                  his attorney to receive for him and in his name of <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> son of
                     <persName>
                              <forename>William</forename> of <surname>Salden</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> in
                  <placeName type="wapentake" key="place_103039">Pykeringlyth</placeName> seisin of one acre of land, as is contained in a certain writing. 
                  Dated at <placeName role="date" key="place_103062">Aton</placeName> in the <placeName role="date" key="place_103384">vale of Pykering</placeName> the 
                  Tuesday after the feast of the translation of St. Thomas, <origDate notBefore="1379-06-22" notAfter="1380-06-21">3 Rich. II</origDate>. 
               </p>
